{
  "phase": "ready",
  "section": "final_review",
  "questions": [],
  "summary": "Recap: Scope/timeline PoC Mar 2026, MVP May 2026. Key risks: video upload/playback reliability, timecode accuracy, and completion lock behavior. Team: single engineer; ad-hoc releases. Test levels for PoC: (1) Frontend unit/functional with Vitest + React Testing Library + MSW, c8 for coverage (targets FE unit ≥75% lines/≥60% branches); (2) Backend unit with JUnit 5 + Mockito, JaCoCo (targets BE unit ≥80% lines/≥70% branches); (3) Backend integration with Spring Boot Test + Testcontainers (PostgreSQL), S3 mocked; exercise all DB-related repositories/services with happy path plus at least one failure path each; (4) End-to-end with Playwright (Chromium-only), running on merges to main against shared staging; real login using Liquibase-seeded users; critical flows covered: upload new version; comment on latest and clicking timecode seeks; viewing non-latest prevents new comments and forces comments to latest; producer marks complete (locks comments/uploads) and can reverse. Deferred to MVP: mutation testing (Backend PIT ≥60%; Frontend Stryker optional), light-touch performance/security/accessibility checks, dependency/secret scanning. Tooling/process: ESLint + Prettier + TypeScript checks via pre-commit (Husky/lint-staged); JaCoCo in CI; Playwright traces/screenshots on failure. S3: real bucket for E2E and pre-deploy smoke only; backend integration tests mock S3; unique S3 key prefix per run, test cleanup, plus 7-day lifecycle auto-delete. Quality gates: PRs require lint, typecheck, FE/BE unit tests meeting thresholds, and backend integration tests; self-approval allowed but PR required. CI: E2E runs only on merges to main against staging. Pre-deployment: Liquibase validate/migrate, S3 write/read smoke, and brief smoke of core flows; defined rollback plan (DB backup + app rollback). Post-deployment: immediate smoke (health, login, upload, comment seek, complete/uncomplete) with automatic rollback on failure. Testing principles: test-after development; flaky E2E allowed 1 retry then fail, quarantine with issue and 48h fix window; E2E data isolation (own entities, unique S3 prefix, cleanup); user-centric Given/When/Then naming, tests colocated with code, lightweight Test Notes documenting critical E2E flows and seeded users. Please confirm to save this test strategy."
}
